Redsive is a new type of antiviral drug developed by Gilid, which was originally used for the treatment of diseases caused by Ebola and Marburger virus.
Later it was also demonstrated that Redsive may inhibit other single-chain RNA viruses, including MERS and SARS viruses.
Based on these reasons, Gilid has delivered the drug to China for two clinical trials on SARS-CoV-2-infected people and the results are hopeful.
Additionally, it has been recommended to use Baricetin, α-interferon, Lopinawe/Litonawe and Libavelin as potential therapies for patients with acute respiratory symptoms.
After the combined treatment of Lopinawe/Litonawe, diarrhea, nausea, vomiting, liver damage and other adverse reactions may occur.
Interactions between these treatments and other medications that the patient uses should be carefully monitored.
